    <section id="main-content">
        <article id="mission">
            <h2>Our Mission</h2>
            <p>My Choices Foundation is committed to ending human trafficking and gender-based violence through prevention strategies, advocacy, victim support, and empowering survivors.</p>
            <p>We believe in creating awareness, providing education, rehabilitation, and fostering a safe environment for those affected.</p>
        </article>

        <article id="programs">
            <h2>Our Programs</h2>
            <p>1. <strong>Empowerment Workshops:</strong> Providing education and training to vulnerable communities to prevent trafficking and abuse. These workshops cover topics such as self-defense, rights awareness, and vocational training.</p>
            <p>2. <strong>Rescue & Rehabilitation:</strong> Rescuing victims of trafficking and providing them with shelter, medical care, counseling, and skill development programs to help them reintegrate into society.</p>
            <p>3. <strong>Legal Advocacy:</strong> Supporting survivors through legal proceedings, providing legal aid, and advocating for stronger laws and policies to combat trafficking and protect victims.</p>
        </article>

        <article id="helpline">
            <h2>Helpline Numbers</h2>
            <p>Are you in a healthy relationship?</p>
            <p>If you or someone you know needs assistance or support, please reach out to our helpline numbers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Domestic Violence Helpline:</strong>1800 21209131</li>
                <li><strong>Sex Trafficking Helpline:</strong>1800 419 8588</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
        
